# Shadcn/UI Component Guidelines

## Configuration
- Shadcn/UI is configured with [components.json](mdc:components.json)
- Components are located in `src/components/ui/` directory
- Use the `@/components/ui/` import path

## Available Components
- Button: Use for all interactive elements
- Card: Use for content containers and layouts
- Input: Use for form inputs
- Label: Use for form labels
- Form: Use for form validation and handling
- Dialog: Use for modals and overlays
- DropdownMenu: Use for dropdown menus
- Avatar: Use for user profile pictures
- Badge: Use for status indicators and tags

## Component Usage
- Import components from `@/components/ui/`
- Use TypeScript for all component props
- Follow Shadcn/UI prop patterns and variants
- Extend components when needed, don't modify source files

## Styling Components
- Components use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use variant props for different styles (default, secondary, outline, etc.)
- Use size props for different sizes (sm, md, lg)
- Customize through CSS variables in globals.css

## Form Components
- Use Form component with react-hook-form for validation
- Use Input with Label for form fields
- Use Button for form submissions
- Implement proper error handling and loading states

## Layout Components
- Use Card for content sections
- Use CardHeader, CardContent, CardTitle, CardDescription
- Combine with Tailwind utilities for custom layouts
- Use consistent spacing and typography

## Best Practices
- Don't modify the source component files
- Create wrapper components for custom functionality
- Use composition over inheritance
- Maintain accessibility standards

